According to a report by Intel Market Research, the global Cocoa Butter Substitutes (CBS) Market was valued at USD 442 million in 2024 and is projected to reach USD 574 million by 2034, expanding at a CAGR of 3.9% during the forecast period.
The market is experiencing steady growth as food manufacturers increasingly adopt cocoa butter substitutes to reduce production costs while maintaining product quality and functionality. Cocoa Butter Substitutes (CBS), primarily lauric-based hardened vegetable fats, are widely used in compound chocolate, bakery coatings, biscuits, wafers, and confectionery products due to their excellent stability, ease of processing, and non-tempering characteristics.
